						<summary>

						<p>MADRAS.</p>						

						<p>On Slab in the ground outside the Government Museum building.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarāja I Year 23.</hi></p>						

						<p>The stone containing this inscription is mutilated. Fragments of the <hi rend="italic">meykīrtti</hi> commencing with <hi rend="italic">Tirumagaḷ pōla</hi> of the king are available at the beginning of the inscription. It is also clear that it records an endowment of sheep for a perpetual lamp. Kōvūr in Māṅgāḍu-nāḍu is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
